ENTRY       EC 1.10.99.3                Enzyme
NAME        violaxanthin de-epoxidase;
            VDE
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on diphenols and related substances as donors;
            With other acceptors
SYSNAME     violaxanthin:ascorbate oxidoreductase
REACTION    violaxanthin + 2 L-ascorbate = zeaxanthin + 2 L-dehydroascorbate + 2 H2O (overall reaction) [RN:R10055];
            (1a) violaxanthin + L-ascorbate = antheraxanthin + L-dehydroascorbate + H2O [RN:R07178];
            (1b) antheraxanthin + L-ascorbate = zeaxanthin + L-dehydroascorbate + H2O [RN:R07179]
ALL_REAC    R07178 R07179 R10055
SUBSTRATE   violaxanthin [CPD:C08614];
            L-ascorbate [CPD:C00072];
            antheraxanthin [CPD:C08579]
PRODUCT     zeaxanthin [CPD:C06098];
            L-dehydroascorbate [CPD:C05422];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            antheraxanthin [CPD:C08579]
COMMENT     Along with EC 1.14.13.90, zeaxanthin epoxidase, this enzyme forms part of the xanthophyll (or violaxanthin) cycle for controlling the concentration of zeaxanthin in chloroplasts. It is activated by a low pH of the thylakoid lumen (produced by high light intensity). Zeaxanthin induces the dissipation of excitation energy in the chlorophyll of the light-harvesting protein complex of photosystem II. In higher plants the enzyme reacts with all-trans-diepoxides, such as violaxanthin, and all-trans-monoepoxides, but in the alga Mantoniella squamata, only the diepoxides are good substrates.
HISTORY     EC 1.10.99.3 created 2005
